    public class ActivityImpl
extends com.faizsiegeln.njams.messageformat.v4.logmessage.Activity
implements Activity
    This is internal implementation of the Activity. It is a extension of the MesasgeFormat activity, and provided functionality for easy chaining activities.
    Author:
    pnientiedt

      • setEventStatus

        public void setEventStatus(Integer eventStatus)
        Sets the EventStatus for this job. An EventStatus can be 0 for INFO 1 for SUCCESS 2 for WARNING 3 for ERROR or null for no eventStatus. Anything else will change nothing. The status of the corresponding job to this activity will be set to SUCCESS, WARNING or ERROR likewise. For INFO only the eventStatus will be set, but the job status will stay the same.
        Specified by:
        setEventStatus in interface com.faizsiegeln.njams.messageformat.v4.logmessage.interfaces.IActivity
        Overrides:
        setEventStatus in class com.faizsiegeln.njams.messageformat.v4.logmessage.Activity
        Parameters:
        eventStatus - eventStatus to set.
